      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why Enzyme-Based Deodorizing Works</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Most national turf guides recommend antimicrobial infill for pet odor. That advice doesn't apply in Las Cruces. There's so much airborne sand here that it naturally settles into turf fibers on its own — paying for manufactured infill is a wasted expense. And once any infill is down, it compacts hard and can't be swapped out.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Enzyme-based deodorizers work differently. They break down the organic compounds that actually cause odor — uric acid, ammonia, bacteria — at a molecular level. The smell doesn't get masked. It gets eliminated. And because it's a treatment, not a permanent material, you can repeat it as often as your yard needs it.</p>
